{"article_id":"mmJLb1DCWHOp9g8F","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Weeks later ,","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"the Sunshine State has emerged as a coronavirus epicenter .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Nearly 1 out of every 100 residents is infected with the virus ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"hospital intensive care units are full or filling up ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"and big-name visitors","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"who chose Florida for their first post-isolation events","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"are now mired in questions and controversies about safety .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Amid escalating infections , Florida ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"once held up by President Trump as a model","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"for how to manage the novel coronavirus ,","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"is faring poorly .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Residents worry","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"the situation will get much worse .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Florida is now one of a handful of states","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"whose spiking numbers are driving a major resurgence of the virus in the United States ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"which is approaching 3 million cases .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"Gov . Ron DeSantis","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"( R )","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"has downplayed the growing outbreak in Florida ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"expanded testing is responsible for more positive results","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"and emphasizing","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that many new infections are among younger people","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"less likely to experience the worst effects of the virus .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"On Tuesday there were 213,794 cases of the coronavirus in Florida ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"according to data .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The state has tallied a record number of cases over the past week ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"averaging 8,766 a day ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"according to Post data .","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"In a sign of intensifying trouble , 52 intensive care units across more than a third of the state ' s counties had reached capacity by Tuesday ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"according to data","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"released by the state ' s Agency for Health Care Administration .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Another 17 hospitals had also run out of regular beds .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"The state has \" abundant capacity , \"","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"DeSantis said at a news conference Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Some nurses at Good Samaritan Medical Center in West Palm Beach have been working 18 hours instead of the usual 12","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"because of overnight staffing shortages ,","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"according to a nurse","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"who spoke on the condition of anonymity","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"for fear","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"of jeopardizing her job .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Patients are being treated in an open area","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"cordoned off by curtains","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that is typically used for quick medical consultations ,","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Ryan Lieber , a spokesman for the hospital , denied","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"employees were being asked to work 18-hour shifts ,","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"adding in a statement ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"\" Patients are being treated in areas of the hospital","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"which are considered appropriate for their care , and respectful of their privacy at all times . \"","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"Florida Education Commissioner Richard Corcoran late Monday ordered","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"that the state ' s schools open for in-person instruction next month ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"igniting fears","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"that a new round of classroom interactions would lead to a new round of infections .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"\" We want to proceed with caution ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"but unfortunately the governor continues to deny the science , \"","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"said Fedrick Ingram , president of the Florida Education Association .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"\" The trend over the last 30 days has been astronomical .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"We ' re in regression ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"we ' re going backward .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"In terms of the amount of cases , we are literally going backward as a state . \"","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"Hospital leaders , lawmakers , physicians , epidemiologists , advocates and others familiar with the state ' s response said","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"a false sense of security set in","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"when grim predictions about the virus ' s spread in Florida did not come to pass in March and April .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"DeSantis declared victory ,","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"attending a laudatory news conference at the White House with President Trump .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"The editor of National Review wrote an editorial","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"titled","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"\" Where does Ron DeSantis go","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"to get his apology ? \"","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"But observers maintain","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"the state then failed to prepare for a surge of the virus ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"which struck","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"as residents were seeking refuge in air-conditioned indoor spaces ,","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"where the virus is believed to be most easily transmitted .","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"Sports leagues","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"that opted to restart their seasons in Florida","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"will now play in a state","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that is in worse shape","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"than when the pandemic began .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"Many teams are already in the state ,","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"and they face a growing number of critics","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"who believe","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"they should cancel games .","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"The Republican National Convention ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"scheduled to take place in Jacksonville next month ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"faces similar questions about safety .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"In June , the Republican National Committee announced","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"that it would move its convention from a worried Charlotte to a welcoming Jacksonville .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"But","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"as cases mount in the city ,","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"worries have crept in .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"\" My concern has grown since a week ago .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"It has gotten worse , \"","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"said Tommy Hazouri , the Democratic president of the city council and a former Jacksonville mayor .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"Hazouri was initially supportive of his city ' s effort","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"to secure the convention .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"\" It is time to accept reality ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"and no one can be in denial about what is going on , \"","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"\" At some point our council and the leaders in this community have to draw a line in the sand on where we need to be going . \"","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"Several hundred doctors have signed a petition","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"that says","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"the convention needs stronger safety measures .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Nancy Staats , a retired anesthesiologist","depth":11},{"id":105,"text":"who lives in the Jacksonville area ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"she hoped","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"a few dozen doctors would sign the petition","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"she helped circulate .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Within three days , nearly 500 had added their names .","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"\" We ' re really focused on the health and well-being of the citizens of our city and state now .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"That ' s still six or seven weeks off","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"and we ' re still climbing scarily , rapidly , \"","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Staats said .","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"\" This is about people ' s lives ,","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"including the attendees of this event . \"","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"NBA and Major League Soccer teams have already landed in Orlando ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"hoping","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"they play in a coronavirus-free bubble .","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"A day before resuming summer tournaments ,","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"FC Dallas was sent home","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"after a coach and 10 players tested positive for the coronavirus at the same Disney sports complex","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that will host the NBA later this month .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"Nashville SC ' s first game Wednesday was postponed","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"after five players tested positive for the virus","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"and four tests were inconclusive .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"\" I am excited to play , \"","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"D.C. United midfielder Julian Gressel said .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"\" I ' m not excited about the part","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"that obviously puts us at risk . \"","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"At a Fortune magazine virtual forum Tuesday , NBA Commissioner Adam Silver acknowledged","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"that Florida ' s situation has significantly deteriorated in recent weeks .","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"\" On paper and dealing with our experts , this should work , \"","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"\" But we shall see .","depth":6},{"id":136,"text":"I ' m confident","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"- based on the positive cases","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"we ' re seeing from our players and the general public around the country -","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"that it will be safer on this campus than off this campus . \"","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"Still , numerous NBA stars have expressed deep concern about the health situation in Florida .","depth":4},{"id":141,"text":"More than a dozen players have decided to sit out the restart for various reasons .","depth":4},{"id":142,"text":"Disney World has announced","depth":6},{"id":143,"text":"it would begin to allow visitors back into the Magic Kingdom this week .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"Disneyland in Anaheim , Calif. , said","depth":6},{"id":145,"text":"it would remain closed .","depth":6},{"id":146,"text":"The Actors ' Equity Association , a union","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"that represents more than 700 Disney World stage managers and actors ,","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"has locked horns with the amusement park ,","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"it has failed to provide a coronavirus testing plan","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"that would help prevent performers from passing the coronavirus onto others .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"\" You certainly can ' t wave Mickey ' s magic wand","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"and say","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"that Florida isn ' t a central hot spot right now , \"","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"said Kate Shindle , the union ' s president .","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"\" Personally , as the president of the organization","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"that is fighting for the safety of these performers ,","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"I ' m mystified by the fact","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"that Disney is attempting to open the park right now . \"","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"The new , high-profile risks threaten to compound problems","depth":7},{"id":161,"text":"Florida has faced from the beginning of the pandemic .","depth":7},{"id":162,"text":"There has been a rise in cases","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"affecting older Floridians as well as those","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"living in nursing homes and other long-term care facilities ,","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"said Jeff Johnson , Florida director of AARP .","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"\" I don ' t see how that doesn ' t mushroom at some point , \"","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"he said ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"noting","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"that staff at the facilities live in communities","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"still grappling with the virus ,","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"sometimes working second or third jobs","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"that involve interactions with people of diverse age groups .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Testing sites across the state are seeing shortages ,","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"and the wait time for results is now as long as 10 days ,","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"said U.S. Rep. Ted Deutch , a Democrat","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"representing a swath of the coast","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"stretching from Broward County to Palm Beach County .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"The problems stem ,","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"he said ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"from the apparent failure","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"to produce a testing plan","depth":11},{"id":182,"text":"as required by Congress ,","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"or at least to unveil any of its details .","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"He has been asking for details ,","depth":10},{"id":185,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"but has been rebuffed by the state health department ,","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"whose deadline was extended from June 15 to Friday .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"The health department did not respond to requests for comment .","depth":8},{"id":189,"text":"There were also acute shortages of the antiviral drug remdesivir in parts of the state ,","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"causing Democratic members of Florida ' s congressional delegation to send a letter Tuesday to Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar","depth":8},{"id":191,"text":"asking him to speed the shipment of emergency supplies .","depth":8},{"id":192,"text":"\" Staff capacity is strained ;","depth":9},{"id":193,"text":"the number of available ICU beds are dwindling ;","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"and we are running out of remdesivir . . . \"","depth":10},{"id":195,"text":"the lawmakers wrote ,","depth":8},{"id":196,"text":"warning","depth":8},{"id":197,"text":"that \" people will die","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"without replenished stock . \"","depth":9},{"id":199,"text":"Amid the array of old and new concerns , teachers across Florida learned","depth":7},{"id":200,"text":"they would have to begin preparing their classrooms for an influx of students .","depth":7},{"id":201,"text":"In Palm Beach County , first-grade teacher Cara Conlogue ,","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"who teaches at Coral Reef Elementary School west of Lake Worth Beach ,","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"the messages","depth":11},{"id":205,"text":"coming from the state","depth":11},{"id":206,"text":"are frightening and confusing .","depth":10},{"id":207,"text":"\" The science is going in one direction ,","depth":12},{"id":208,"text":"and conditions are getting worse ,","depth":12},{"id":209,"text":"and the politicians are going in the opposite direction , \"","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"Conlogue said .","depth":10},{"id":211,"text":"\" I can ' t wrap my head around it .","depth":10},{"id":212,"text":"If it wasn ' t safe for us","depth":13},{"id":213,"text":"when there were 100 cases ,","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"how can it be safe for us","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"when we have thousands and thousands of cases ?","depth":13},{"id":216,"text":"I don ' t get that logic . \"","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"\" I ' ve spoken with a lot of my teacher friends ,","depth":10},{"id":218,"text":"and a lot of them don ' t want to go back , \"","depth":10},{"id":219,"text":"she continued .","depth":9},{"id":220,"text":"\" We love our students ,","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"we miss them ,","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"and we love our jobs .","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"But we don ' t feel safe . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":447,"left":354,"right":446,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":354,"left":236,"right":353,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":225,"right":235,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":225,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":235,"left":229,"right":234,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":2,"right":228,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":228,"left":3,"right":227,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":227,"left":226,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":226,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":234,"left":232,"right":233,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":231,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":231,"left":7,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":230,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":233,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":353,"left":297,"right":352,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":246,"right":296,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":238,"right":245,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":238,"left":13,"right":237,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":14,"right":15,"rel